<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bootstrap Installation in Ruby on Rails</title>
    <link href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/5.3.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        .bg-custom {
            background-color: White;
        }
        .bg-inner {
            background-color: #DDEEF2; 
        }
        .bg-inner-inner{
           /*background-color: #80BDB8;*/
           background-color: #E3ECFF;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-custom">
    <div class="container my-5">
        <div class="card shadow-sm bg-inner">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h1 class="card-title text-center mb-4">Bootstrap Installation in Ruby on Rails</h1>
                <p><strong>This is a small guide on how to integrate boostrap 5 into the rails 7 pipeline:</strong></p>
                <ol class="list-group list-group-numbered">
                    <li class="list-group-item bg-inner-inner">
                        Create new ruby project using
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-white p-3 rounded"><code>$ rails new app_name -bootstrap</code></pre>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item bg-inner-inner">
                        Install js bundling rails and check that turbo-rails and stimulus are installed. (check in the gemfile)
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-white p-3 rounded"><code>bundle add jsbundling-rails</code></pre>
                        <p>If turbo-rails and stimulus are not installed, install them using:</p>
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-white p-3 rounded"><code>yarn add @hotwired/turbo-rails
yarn add @hotwired/stimulus</code></pre>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item bg-inner-inner">
                        Edit:
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-white p-3 rounded"><code>--- a/app/javascript/application.js
+++ b/app/javascript/application.js
-import "controllers"
+import "./controllers";

--- a/app/javascript/controllers/index.js
+++ b/app/javascript/controllers/index.js
-import { application } from "controllers/application"
-
-// Eager load all controllers defined in the import map under controllers/**/*_controller
-import { eagerLoadControllersFrom } from "@hotwired/stimulus-loading"
-eagerLoadControllersFrom("controllers", application)
-
-// Lazy load controllers as they appear in the DOM (remember not to preload controllers in import map!)
-// import { lazyLoadControllersFrom } from "@hotwired/stimulus-loading"
-// lazyLoadControllersFrom("controllers", application)
+import { application } from "./application";</code></pre>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item bg-inner-inner">
                        Add js bundling rails
                        <pre class="bg-dark text-white p-3 rounded"><code>./bin/rails javascript:install:esbuild</code></pre>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <p class="text-center">Credits to <a href="https://mixandgo.com/learn/ruby-on-rails/how-to-install-bootstrap" target="_blank">Mix & Go</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/5.3.0/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

